algorithms.graphs

Class StarStructure

  • java.lang.Object
    • algorithms.graphs.StarStructure

  • public class StarStructure
extends java.lang.Object
    implementing a star structure and related methods following the algorithms presented as pseudocode in 
     Comparing Stars: On Approximating Graph Edit Distance
   Zeng, Tung, Wang, Feng, & Zhou 2009, 
   Proceedings of the VLDB Endowment, Volume 2, Issue 1,
   August 2009 pp 25–36
   https://doi.org/10.14778/1687627.1687631
    Additionally have added edge labels and modifications to the edit distance costs for them. For use with attributed graphs. Fernandez & Valiente 2001: Attributed relational graphs, introduced in 􏶵Tsai and Fu, 1979), extend the notion of labeled graph by allowing the value of several attributes as labels of vertices and edges.
    Author:
    nichole

      • sortAndSet

        protected void sortAndSet(int rIdx,
                          int rLabel,
                          int[] vLabels,
                          int[] eLabels,
                          int[] vIndexes)
        node and edge labeling functions which can be overridden with specialization. default is to sort but not to alter the values in vLabels and eLabels. This method sorts vLabels, eLabels, and the array of original indexes [0, 1, 2, ..vLabels.length - 1] by ascending sort on vLabels. All results are stored in this instance. NOTE: the design uses specialization of labeling, but could be refactored to use composition.
        Parameters:
        rIdx -
        rLabel -
        vLabels -
        eLabels -
        vIndexes - indexes of the vertexes of vLabels in the context of the original graph g.
